 An Iyaganku, Ibadan Chief Magistrates’ Court yesterday ordered that 23-year-old Mohammed Abdullahi, who allegedly abducted and defiled a 15-year-old-girl, be remanded in a correctional facility pending legal advice. Chief Magistrate I. O. Osho, who did not take the suspect’s plea,  ordered that he be remanded in Agodi Correctional Centre.  She adjourned the matter until May 26, for mention. Earlier, prosecution counsel, Inspector Foluke Adedosu told the court that Abdullahi on February 9 in Apete , Ibadan, abducted a girl, 15, and defiled her. She alleged that Abdullahi met the minor on social media and invited her to his residence. 